{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566541","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566541"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18840"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17656892","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17656892"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:20:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:20:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18840"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18840","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18840"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.97,0,0.01,0.01,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11573"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112698"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11573","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11573"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18840"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94731"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1027"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3032"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11297"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27239"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27244"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30432"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32248"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35059"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45799"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46230"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112698","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112698"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman presents to her General Practitioner at a rural practice with symptoms of depression following the recent death of her spouse. During the consultation, she becomes emotional and expresses feelings of loneliness. The General Practitioner feels sympathetic towards her situation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes appropriate professional boundary maintenance in this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Schedule regular follow-up appointments within clinic hours","Share traumatic personal experiences with patient","Provide additional support through email","Arrange home visits outside normal practice hours","Make unscheduled weekly courtesy calls to check progress"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eschedule regular follow-up appointments within clinic hours\u003C/strong\u003E. This maintains professional boundaries while ensuring consistent care and support through appropriate channels. Regular appointments allow for:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProper clinical assessment and monitoring\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EClear documentation of the therapeutic relationship\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStructured referral to additional services if needed\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMaintenance of work-life boundaries for the doctor\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEqual access to care for all patients\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe inappropriate actions are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EShare traumatic personal experiences with patient\u003C/strong\u003E is not the most appropriate answer. Self-disclosure can blur professional boundaries and shift focus from the patient. It may create inappropriate expectations or dependencies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvide additional support through email\u003C/strong\u003E creates inappropriate access and compromises professional boundaries. Email communication risks confidentiality breaches and creates unrealistic expectations of constant availability.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArrange home visits outside normal practice hours\u003C/strong\u003E represents a significant boundary violation by providing care outside the structured clinical setting. This creates role confusion and potentially compromises the doctor-patient relationship.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMake unscheduled weekly courtesy calls to check progress\u003C/strong\u003E is not the most correct option. Regular contact outside clinic hours represents a boundary crossing that could create unrealistic expectations and compromise the therapeutic relationship. It also fails to protect practitioner wellbeing by blurring work-life boundaries and potentially leading to burnout.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProfessional boundaries protect both the doctor and patient by maintaining clear roles, ensuring objectivity, preventing exploitation or dependency, facilitating appropriate referral pathways, and protecting the doctor\u0027s professional and personal wellbeing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is important to acknowledge that maintaining professional boundaries can be more challenging in rural communities where social and professional roles often overlap. However, even in rural settings, structured clinical appointments remain the most appropriate way to provide care while maintaining professional standards.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Professional boundaries protect both doctors and patients by maintaining appropriate therapeutic relationships.","Doctors must not pursue social or personal relationships with patients or their close family members, even in rural settings.","Therapeutic relationships should be maintained within the clinical setting with appropriate referral pathways.","Clear documentation and structured follow-up within clinic hours helps maintain professional boundaries in all practice settings."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94731"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18840"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94731","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94731"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-04T08:20:07+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-04T08:21:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11573"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112698"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"t